The paper presents a framework for understanding the semantics of visual scenes using ontologies and Prolog. This involves knowledge representation, interpretation rules, and a SceneInterpreter engine. The paper also mentions the use of multiagent systems and experimentation in the domain of prehistoric rock art. Based on these factors, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (artificial intelligence), cs.CL (computation and language), and cs.LG (machine learning). The use of visual scenes and ontologies also suggests cs.CV (computer vision) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the experimentation in a specific domain (prehistoric rock art) could also place the paper in the cs.IR (information retrieval) sub-category.
